WEBVTT

00:00:02.498 --> 00:00:08.087
[The Universe in Verse]

00:00:09.213 --> 00:00:10.381
[Prelude]

00:00:10.757 --> 00:00:12.717
In 1908,

00:00:12.759 --> 00:00:14.385
Henrietta Swan Leavitt,

00:00:14.427 --> 00:00:16.971
one of the women known
as the Harvard Computers,

00:00:17.013 --> 00:00:19.515
who changed our understanding
of the universe

00:00:19.557 --> 00:00:21.726
long before they could vote,

00:00:21.726 --> 00:00:26.189
was cataloging photographic plates
at the Harvard College Observatory,

00:00:26.230 --> 00:00:30.735
single-handedly analyzing
2,000 variable stars --